<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN"
  "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  Hardened Runtime entitlements for the Poker Solver .app bundle.

  Justification (per Apple "Notarizing macOS Software Before Distribution"):

  - com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit
      NumPy and CPython use JIT-like memory patterns (e.g., ctypes
      trampolines, NumPy SIMD dispatch).  Apple documents this as safe
      for hardened-runtime apps that ship a Python interpreter.

  - com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory
      Required for the embedded CPython interpreter on modern macOS;
      CPython allocates RWX pages for compiled bytecode and ctypes
      callbacks that are not signed by Apple.

  - com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation
      Required because PyInstaller bundles dylibs from PyPI/maturin
      signed by other parties (e.g., NumPy wheels, our own _rust.so
      built by maturin/PyO3).  Without this entitlement, the embedded
      Python interpreter refuses to dlopen those dylibs.

  All three are the minimal set documented in the PR 11 spec (§6.4) and
  are the same set that Briefcase/PyInstaller-packaged Python apps in
  the wild use.  We deliberately do NOT request network entitlements,
  microphone, etc. — the app is local-only.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
